### Backups and Restore:  

1. User sends a file with the db dump and imports this dump (in the site creation). / 5. User wants to restore a specific file from a daily backup.  

  Overview:  
    ![](data:image/png;base64,)  

  Pipeline drupal-deploy:  

      DUMP_ORIGING_S3_URL = needs to be informed, in the zip format, with a unique file inside (the Drupal schema dump.sql).  

1.1. Exclusive pipeline for user sends a file with the db dump and imports this dump (site already exists and maintaining Drupal Admin User).  

  Overview:  
    ![](data:image/png;base64,)  

  Pipeline drupal-restore-from-bucket:  


![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  


    CLUSTER = cluster of the site wich will receive the dump.  
    DUMP_ORIGING_S3_URL = needs to be informed, in the zip format, with a unique file inside (the Drupal schema dump.sql).  
    SITE_CNAME = name of the site already up in the AWS that will receive the dump.  
    CONTAINER_DB_NAME = database name that will receive the dump.  


2. User wants the db dump downloaded.  

  This cenario will be comply by the UI.  

  Backup files available in "s3://$BUCKET_NAME/cms/${TYPE_PROJECT}/${CONTAINER_DB_NAME}/backups/snapshot-${TIME}.zip".  

3. Deploying a new site and optionaly clone database from another AWS site (in the same cluster).  

    Overview:  

      ![](data:image/png;base64,)  

  Pipeline drupal-deploy:  

    SITE_CNAME = needs be informed to upate URL in the new site.  
    DUMP_ORIGIN = database name of origin site to make dump and restore on the new site.  


4. User wants to schedule a daily backup.  

  Overview:  

    ![](data:image/png;base64,)  

  Pipeline drupal-deploy:  

    ![](data:image/png;base64,)  

    BACKUP_INTERVAL = interval options to choose at the deploy site, the dump will be storaged at bucket as "s3://$BUCKET_NAME/cms/${TYPE_PROJECT}/${CONTAINER_DB_NAME}/backups/snapshot-${TIME}.zip"  

6. Exclusive pipeline for clone databases (both sites already up and in the same cluster, maintaining Drupal Admin of the site destination).  

  Overview:  

    ![](data:image/png;base64,)  

  Pipeline drupal-clone-databases:  


![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  


    CLUSTER = cluster of both sites, origin and destiny.  

    ORIGIN = database origin.  

    DESTINATION = database destination.  

    SITE_CNAME = site name destination.

7.Exclusive pipeline make backup.  

  Overview:  

![](data:image/png;base64,)  

  Pipeline drupal-make-backup:  


![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  


  CONTAINER_DB_NAME = database name to make the dump and store on S3 bucket.
